<TITLE> Suicide bombing kills 7 in Pakistan's Swat - police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MINGORA, Mar 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide bombing attack on security forces in Pakistan's Swat Valley on Saturday killed at least seven people and wounded 13, police said. The assault near a security checkpost came a day after a suicide attack on the military killed at least 45 people in the city of Lahore. "The bomber was in a rickshaw," said Qazi Ghulam Farooq, Mingora city police chief. Militants have gone on the offensive again after a relative lull in violence. The blast in Mingora, capital of Swat Valley, was the sixth blast this week, adding to pressure on unpopular President Asif Ali Zardari. Pakistan launched a security offensive in Swat last year and said militants, who had turned it into a bastion where they imposed an extreme version of Islam, had been cleared o
